 it </div><div class="t m7ca x48 h28 y1757 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that had the effect of hardening Pharaoh&apos;s heart? </div><div class="t mb93 x48 h28 y158e ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ans.—The rejection of light from God. See notes. </div><div class="t m167 x28 h28 y1bef ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">24. </div><div class="t me20 x53 h28 y268 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">With what scripture is this in harmony? </div><div class="t m624 x48 h28 y655 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Isa. 26 : 1o. </div><div class="t m167 x28 h28 y1900 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">25. </div><div class="t m5fc x53 h28 y68c ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is it that makes wicked persons more </div><div class="t m110f x5d h28 yb43 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">settled in their determination to sin? Eccl. 8 :it. </div><div class="t m167 x28 h28 y658 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">26. </div><div class="t mf22 x53 h28 y18cd ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">After the sixth plague, what did the Lord </div><div class="t m614 x5d h28 y1594 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">say was the reason he had preserved Pharaoh for </div><div class="t m100c x5d h28 y6b0 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">so long a time? Ex. 9: 55, i6. See note. </div><div class="t m167 x28 h28 y6b1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">27. </div><div class="t m820 x3f h28 y6b1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When God&apos;s judgments are in the land, </div><div class="t m1ca x48 h28 y1773 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for what purpose is it ? Isa. 26 :9. </div><div class="t m135a x87 h28 y2ab ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES. </div><div class="t mab1 x28 h28 y1b4e ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">GOD knows the hearts of all men (Acts 15 : 8; </div><div class="t m33e x5d h28 y5f2 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">John </div><div class="t m14a x55 h4 y5f2 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 : </div><div class="t m7c7 x7e h28 y1809 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">25), and so he knew the full stubborn-</div><div class="t m59a x48 h28 y1fac ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ness of Pharaoh&apos;s nature before he sent Moses to </div><d